<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;line-height:normal'><b><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:24.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Hypercortisolism</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>What
is hypercortisolism</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Hypercortisolism is a
syndrome in which there is excessive secretion of hormones from the adrenal
cortex.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The
disease is also known as</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Hyperadrenocorticism;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Itsenko-Cushing's syndrome;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Cushing's disease;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>cushingoid.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>In English, the disease
is called:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Cushing's syndrome;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>hypercortisolism;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>hyperadrenocorticism.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Causes</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Hypercorticism occurs
as a result of excessive synthesis of adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH) or
increased synthesis of cortisol.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Increased synthesis of
ACTH is observed in the following pathologies:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>pituitary adenoma (Itsenko-Cushing's disease);</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>dysfunction of the hypothalamus (excessive synthesis of
corticoliberin);</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>ectopic (not in the typical location) ACTH tumors.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Excess production of cortisol
is observed in tumors of the adrenal glands.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Cushing's syndrome may
develop during the treatment of diseases that require the appointment of high
doses of glucocorticoid drugs.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Who is at risk</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>The average age of onset of the disease is 20-40 years.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Patients taking long-term glucocorticoid drugs.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>How
often does it occur</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Incidence data range
from 0.2 to 5 cases per million.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Symptoms</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Weakness, irritability, memory loss.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Obesity (deposition of fat on the chest and upper abdomen).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Increase in blood pressure.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Bright blush of cheeks (matronism).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Burgundy lines.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Headache.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Decreased libido.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>In women, there is hirsutism (the appearance of male pattern
hair), male pattern baldness.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Acne, skin hyperpigmentation.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Slow healing of wounds, the appearance of hematomas / ecchymosis.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Decreased bone mineral density (low-traumatic fractures).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Growth retardation in children.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Diagnosis of the disease</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Collection of anamnesis</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>A detailed survey of
the patient about the existing complaints, the duration of the onset of symptoms.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Clinical examination</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>General examination with an assessment of the function of vital
organs (emphasis on blood pressure).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Examination by systems with the detection of clinical
manifestations.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Laboratory
research</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>At least two of these
screening tests are recommended:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>determination of the level of cortisol in the saliva collected by
the patient at bedtime (reflects a violation of the rhythm of cortisol
synthesis);</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>test with dexamethasone - a study of cortisol in the blood serum
in the morning after taking 1 mg of dexamethasone at bedtime (reflects the
preservation of a negative feedback in healthy people, that is, suppression of
the secretion of ACTH and cortisol in response to the administration of
exogenous glucocorticoids);</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>determination of the level of cortisol in daily urine
(demonstrates daily production of cortisol).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Instrumental diagnostic
methods</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>MRI of the brain (to detect pituitary adenoma).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Ultrasound of the adrenal glands (to exclude a tumor of the
adrenal glands).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>MSCT (multispiral computed tomography) of the body (the course of
Cushing's syndrome without a tumor focus in the brain or adrenal glands).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
